	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Based in Limpopo, The Rhino Orphanage is the only one of its
kind around the globe. Here, passionate volunteers treat and understand the
rhinos in order to protect the species from going extinct. The moving journey is covered in an M-Net series, The Wild
Ones. The documentary gives viewers a sneak peek into the lives of Rhinos
beings poached and those looking after them. The series, which premiers on M-Net at 15h00 on 6 May,
provides an insight into the love and care that goes into keeping Rhinos safe
and secure. Drum was invited to see the work done first hand. See the touching video of baby rhino Mofalodi below: 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  